Charismatic actor Francis Ng, Best Actor winner at the Golden Horse Awards for The Mission, returns with a new movie that organically blends thriller and comedy together. According to Mainland Chinese director Huang Guangli, this latest production of his can be regarded as an &quot;urban fable&quot; showcasing different facets of urban mentality. Francis Ng stars as mechanic suffering from bad luck. A talented actor to be reckoned with, he brings to live a pathetic urban dweller who seems to be more ill-fated than anyone else in the city. Cherrie Ying (Himalaya Singh) also spices up the film with her charming beauty.

Francis Ng plays an impotent mechanic who is in bad terms with his wife (Liang Jing). He comes across a self-proclaimed fortuneteller (Mainland Chinese TV host Liu Yiwei) who prophesizes that he will have bad luck unless he get rid of those hurting his fortune. This naive mechanic then crashes his car and meets a hot girl in the accident, and then he blows up his boss&amp;#039; (Paul Chun) vehicle, and then he is forced to pay for the his boss&amp;#039; losses, and then he suspects his wife having an
affairs... With all these misfortunes, will he follow the fortuneteller&amp;#039;s advice and kill all those who cause him bad luck?
